thermal: cix: separate the unused SCMI energy-model helper

CIX_THERMAL implements CPU IPA and does not call cix_scmi_register_em().
Do not force the separate GPU-oriented library helper on with CPU IPA.  When
selected explicitly, require its SCMI performance-domain provider and describe
its ACPI/DT fwnode support and the need for a real caller.

diff --git a/drivers/thermal/cix/Kconfig b/drivers/thermal/cix/Kconfig
--- a/drivers/thermal/cix/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/thermal/cix/Kconfig
@@ -6,7 +6,6 @@ config CIX_THERMAL
 	depends on THERMAL && THERMAL_GOV_POWER_ALLOCATOR
 	depends on CPU_FREQ && ENERGY_MODEL
 	depends on ACPI_CPPC_CPUFREQ
-	select CIX_SCMI_ENERGY_MODEL
 	help
 	  Power allocator (IPA) support for CIX platforms, including the
 	  cpu-ipa MMIO driver for per-CPU static/dynamic power, ACPI thermal
@@ -21,7 +20,12 @@ config CIX_SCMI_ENERGY_MODEL
 	depends on ENERGY_MODEL
 	depends on CIX_THERMAL
 	depends on ARM_SCMI_PROTOCOL
+	depends on ARM_SCMI_PERF_DOMAIN
 	help
-	  It uses SCMI Message Protocol and SCMI performance domain helpers
-	  to register Energy Model (EM) for Cix platforms. Supports both
-	  genpd-bound devices and DT-based domain ID parsing.
+	  Provide the cix_scmi_register_em() helper for a device driver that
+	  needs to register an Energy Model from an SCMI performance domain.
+	  The helper obtains the domain from generic firmware-node properties,
+	  so both DT and equivalent ACPI _DSD data are supported.
+
+	  This is a library helper, not a standalone driver. It has no runtime
+	  effect unless a device driver calls cix_scmi_register_em().
